def: "Sensitivity to the carbon content in the growth medium. It plays an important role in the synthesis of various inorganic and organic metabolites such as carbohydrates, lipids, amino acids and peptides and plays a role in various metabolic processes." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: carbon sensitivity

comment: Observed by general growth conditions in relation to standard resistant and susceptible checks. Since some soil problems are very heterogeneous in the field, several replications may be needed to obtain precise reading. Leaf is counted as discolored or dead if more than half of its area is discolored or dead.
def: "Plant sensitivity to soils with alkali conditions (pH>7)." [IRRI:SES, TO:moorel]
name: alkali soil sensitivity

def: "Trait of a plant in which the action of the cytotoxic gene used to introduce male sterility is suppressed by the application of a chemical to the plant. Reversion of the sterility allows the RMS parent to be self-fertilized, a step that overcomes the need to remove fertile sib plants prior to making the hybrid cross." [PMID:10645437]
name: reversible male sterility

def: "Sensitivity to the calcium content in the growth medium. Plays an important role in cell wall synthesis and enzyme activities." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: calcium sensitivity

def: "Response by the plant in terms of sensitivity to sulfur content in the growth medium. It is important for synthesis of some amino acid residues." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: sulfur sensitivity

def: "Sensitivity to the potassium ion content in the growth medium. It plays an important role in controlling water by osmosis and also in the metal ion homeostasis." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: potassium sensitivity

def: "Male sterility affected by photoperiod." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: genic male sterility-photoperiod sensitive
synonym: ['"PGMS (related)" RELATED []', '"photoperiod sensitive genic male sterility (related)" RELATED []', '"PPDSNGMS (related)" RELATED []']

def: "Sensitivity to the magnesium content in the growth medium. It is important for chlorophyll biosynthesis and metal ion homeostasis." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: magnesium sensitivity

def: "Sensitivity to the nitrogen content in the growth medium. It is important for protein synthesis, chlorophyll etc." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: nitrogen sensitivity

def: "Sensitivity to the molecular hydrogen or hydrogen ion content in the growth medium. It plays an important role in the synthesis of various inorganic and organic metabolites such as carbohydrates, lipids, amino acids and peptides and plays a role in the energy metabolism, osmolarity,  etc." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: hydrogen sensitivity
synonym: ['"hydrogen ion sensitivity (related)" RELATED []', '"molecular hydrogen sensitivity (related)" RELATED []']

comment: The factors needed for successful test are the presence of sources and vectors, inoculation at the susceptible growth stage of the test plants and favorable environmental conditions.
def: "An assay to determine the resistance exhibited by a plant or a group of plants (population) in response to the disease caused by a mycoplasma-like pathogen infection as compared to the susceptible and/or the reference plants of the same species." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: resistance to disease by mycoplasma-like organism

def: "Average weight of the panicle from the plants or tillers in a given study." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: panicle weight

def: "Sensitivity to the molecular oxygen or reactive oxygen ion content in the growth medium. It plays an important role in the synthesis of various inorganic and organic metabolites such as carbohydrates, lipids, aminoacids and peptides and plays a role in the energy metabolism." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: oxygen sensitivity

def: "Sensitivity to the cobalt content in the growth medium." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: cobalt sensitivity

comment: Includes traits of plant structures (PO:0009011) such as plant cell (PO:0009002), plant organ (PO:0009008), portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007), vascular system (PO:0000034), whole plant (PO:0000003) and seed (PO:0009010), as well as those of plant anatomical spaces (PO:0025117) and portions of plant substance (PO:0025161).
def: "A plant trait (TO:0000387) which is a morphological quality of a plant anatomical entity (PO:0025131) or a constituent cellular component (GO:0005575) contained therein." [GO:0005575, Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, PO:0025131, TO:cooperl]
name: plant morphology trait
synonym: ['"plant architecture trait (related)" RELATED []', '"plant structure trait (related)" RELATED []']

def: "Sensitivity to the boron content in the growth medium. It plays an important role in cell division." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: boron sensitivity

def: "Average height measurements of 10 seedlings, in centimeters from the base of the shoot to the tip of the tallest leaf blade." [IRRI:SES]
name: seedling height

def: "Sensitivity to the copper ion content in the growth medium. Plays a role as cofactor in synthesis of some enzymes important in photosynthesis." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: copper sensitivity

def: "Causal agent: Oebalus pugnax." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: stink bug resistance

def: "Causal agent: species of Sarocladium, Bipolaris, Alternaria, Gerlachia, Fusarium, Phoma, Curvularia, Trichoconiella and Psaudomonas etc. Symptoms: darkening of glumes of spikelets, brown color to black including rotten glumes caused by one or more pathogens. Intensity ranges from sporadic discoloration to discoloration of the whole glume. Severity of grain discoloration can be estimated by counting of grains with more than 25% of glume surface affected." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: fungal infection related grain discoloration

comment: Refer to length PATO:0000122: A 1-D extent quality which is equal to the distance between two points.
def: "A ligule morphology trait (TO:0002748) which is a length of a ligule measured in millimeters from the base of the leaf collar to the tip of the ligule (PO:0020105)." [IRRI:SES, PO:0020105, TO:cooperl]
name: ligule length

def: "Important for nitrate fixation." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: molybdenum sensitivity

comment: An example is CMS-boro in rice.
def: "Abortion at tri-nucleate stage of microspore development." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: aborted tri-nucleate stage

def: "Actual count of the total number of tillers after full heading, Specify if per plant, hill or area." [IRRI:SES]
name: culm number

def: "Number of unfilled florets in a grass inflorescence." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: unfilled grain number
synonym: ['"UNFILGRNB (related)" RELATED []', '"unfilled florets per panicle (related)" RELATED []', '"unfilled grain (related)" RELATED []']

def: "Sensitivity to the chlorine content in the growth medium. Chloride helps regulate the correct pH (acid/alkaline) balance. This is a major electrolyte in the living cell besides sodium and potassium. It is available to the cell mainly in the form of NaCl and KCl salts." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: chlorine sensitivity

def: "A common sedge weed Cyperus iria (rice flatsedge), Cyperus difformis (Small flower umbrella sedge),  Rice field bulrush Scirpus mucronatus, River bulrush Scirpus fluviatilis. Grows as a weed in the rice field. Can be distinguished from grass plant by the leaf shape, venation, stem cross-section and plant shape leaf shape." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, ISBN:9712200299, web:http//www.ipm.ucdavis.edu/PMG/r682700999.html]
name: sedge weed

def: "Sensitivity to the chromium content in the growth medium." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: chromium sensitivity

comment: Evaluated at growth stage:8 in rice.
def: "A panicle morphology trait (TO:0000847) which is the measurement in centimeters from panicle base to tip." [IRRI:SES]
name: panicle length

comment: Refer to length (PATO:0000122): A 1-D extent quality which is equal to the distance between two points.
def: "A grain length (TO:0000734) monitored after dehulling but before polishing. The grain should contain pericarp (PO:0009084)." [IRRI:SES, PO:0009084, TO:moorel]
name: brown rice length

def: "A plant axis morphology trait (TO:0000738) which is a quality of a root (PO:0025025)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, PO:0025025, TO:cooperl]
name: root morphology trait

comment: Scale,  (%), Stigma exsertion; 1- Above 70, Well exserted; 3- 41-70, Moderately well exserted; 5- 21-40, Just exserted; 7- 11-20, Partly exserted; 9- 0-10, Enclosed.  Evaluated at growth stage:6 and 7 in rice.
def: "Trait is monitored by counting number of flowers or florets that have completed anthesis on a given day and showing exserted stigma. Trait expressed as  percent stigma exsertion." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: stigma exsertion
synonym: ['"STIEX (related)" RELATED []', '"stigma exsertion of male sterile lines (related)" RELATED []']

def: "Causal agent: Balanasia oryzae-sativae (Ephelis oryzae). Symptoms: a white mycelial mat ties the panicle branches together so that they emerge as single, small, cylindrical rods." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: udbatta disease resistance

def: "Causal agent: Tilletia barclayana. Symptoms: infected grains show minute black pustules or streaks bursting through the glumes. In severe infection, the rupturing glumes produce short beak-like or spur-like outgrowths." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: kernel smut disease resistance

comment: Branching usually determines the shape and compactness of the inflorescence
def: "An inflorescence morphology trait (TO:0000373) which is the extent of branching. (PO:0009049)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, PO:0009049, TO:moorel]
name: inflorescence branching

comment: Refer to strength (PATO:0001230): A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's power or force.
def: "A stem morphology trait (TO:0000361) which is the strength of a stem (PO:0009047)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES, PO:0009047, TO:moorel]
name: stem strength

def: "An inflorescence morphology trait (TO:0000373) which is the extent of primary branching that usually sets the tone for shape and compactness of the inflorescence (PO:0009049) (rice panicle)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, PO:0009049, TO:moorel]
name: primary branching of inflorescence

def: "Observed under a microscope at magnification 10x10 after staining with 1% iodine potassium iodide (IKI) solution. Samples for pollen are collected from anthers and fixed in 70% alcohol. Two to three anthers are extracted from each floret and pollen grains are squeezed out into the IKI solution drop. At least three fields are used to count the sterile pollen grains; unstained withered, unstained spherical and partially stained round and fertile, from stained round pollen grains. Percentage sterility is calculated as = (unstained withered+unstained spherical+partially stained) x 100/total number of pollen grains in the field including the fertile." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: pollen sterility

def: "Response by the plant in terms of resistivity or sensitivity to the animals infesting them." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: animal damage resistance

comment: Refer to pubescent hair (PATO:0001320): A pilosity quality of being covered with short hairs or soft down.
def: "A leaf lamina morphology trait (TO:0000829) which is the extent of pubescence  (presence of hairs)  on a leaf lamina (PO:0020039)." [IRRI:SES]
name: leaf lamina pubescence
synonym: ['"LBP (related)" RELATED []', '"leaf blade pubescence (related)" RELATED []', '"LFLHR (related)" RELATED []', '"LFLPUBES (related)" RELATED []']

comment: Refer to color (PATO:0000014): A composite chromatic quality composed of hue, saturation and intensity parts.
def: "A stem morphology trait (TO:0000361) which is the color of a stem (PO:0009047)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, PO:0009047, TO:moorel]
name: stem color

comment: It is expected that the herbicide application must not affect the agronomic yield, if any.
def: "A chemical stress sensitivity (TO:0000482) which is the tolerance exhibited by a plant towards the applied herbicide." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, TO:moorel]
name: herbicide sensitivity

def: "Color of the stem node." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: node color

comment: An example is CMS-WA in rice.
def: "Abortion at uni-nucleate stage of microspore development." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: aborted uni-nucleate stage
mimic response
synonym: ['"disease mimic response (related)" RELATED []', '"lesion mimic (related)" RELATED []', '"MIRP (related)" RELATED []']

def: "A whole plant morphology trait (TO:0000398) which is a quality of a plant embryo (PO:0009009)." [PO:0009009, TO:moorel]
name: plant embryo morphology trait

def: "A root morphology trait (TO:0000043) which is the color of a root (PO:0009005)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: root color

def: "Temperature sensitive male sterility, affected by environment." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: genic male sterility-thermo sensitive
synonym: ['"TGMS (related)" RELATED []', '"thermo sensitive genic male sterility (related)" RELATED []']

def: "Measure of percentage of plants that lodged." [IRRI:SES]
name: lodging incidence

comment: In maize this trait is observed for chlorotic tissue between veins or older leaves, causing holes and torn appearance.
def: "Variegated leaf necrosis or scorching observed in response to stresses like drought, insecticides and cold temperature as evidenced by chlorotic and/or necrotic tissue." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: variegated leaf necrosis

comment: Anthocyanin is the red to purple pigments composed of soluble glycosides of anthocyanidins, present in leaves and floral tissue. Usually the pigment is produced under stress conditions. Amounts of anthocyanin produced depend on stored sugar and sunlight. The more stored sugar in the leaf and brighter the autumn days, the more intense red. Anthocyanin production also increases as phosphates move out of the leaves; the lack of phosphates in young leaves can also lead to the production of anthocyanin.
def: "The anthocyanin content in a plant or plant part." [ISBN:198506732]
name: anthocyanin content

comment: Refer to length PATO:0000122: A 1-D extent quality which is equal to the distance between two points.
def: "An awn morphology trait (TO:0002718) which is the length of awn (PO:0025349)." [IRRI:SES, PO:0025349, TO:moorel]
name: awn length

def: "Sensitivity to the manganese content in the growth medium. It is important for activation of some enzymes and role in metal ion homeostasis." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: manganese sensitivity

def: "Causal agent: Magnaporthe grisea." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: blast disease resistance
synonym: ['"blast disease resistance trait (exact)" EXACT []', '"blast disease susceptibility (narrow)" NARROW []']

def: "Response shown by the plant in terms of sensitivity to light stress (quality and quantity of light)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: light sensitivity

comment: Does not include traits of fruit, parts of fruit and adventitious roots which are borne on the shoot.
def: "A collective plant organ structure morphology trait (TO:0000842) which is a quality of a shoot system (PO:0009006)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, PO:0009006, TO:cooperl]
name: shoot system morphology trait

def: "The average dry weight of the root determined in a study." [Gramene:jcl, Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: root dry weight
synonym: ['"rdw (related)" RELATED []', '"rdw/t (related)" RELATED []', '"root dry weight per tiller (related)" RELATED []', '"RTDWT (related)" RELATED []', '"total root dry weight (related)" RELATED []']

def: "A bract morphology trait (TO:0000815) which is a quality of a flower bract (PO:0009034)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, PO:0009034, TO:cooperl]
name: flower bract morphology trait

def: "Sensitivity response shown by the plant grown in either the excess or deficient amount of the micronutrient in the growth medium (soil)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: micronutrient sensitivity

def: "The average dry weight of the root, (for the root part 30cm below the soil surface) determined per tiller in a green house study." [Gramene:jcl, Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: deep root dry weight
synonym: ['"deep root dry weight per tiller (exact)" EXACT []', '"deep root weight (exact)" EXACT []', '"DRTDWT (exact)" EXACT []', '"drw (exact)" EXACT []', '"drw/t (exact)" EXACT []']

def: "Causal agent: Recilia dorsalis (Motschulsky)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: zigzag leafhopper resistance

def: "Its the total number of roots penetrating the hard pans of the soil or the number of roots penetrated through the wax-petrolatum layer measured at 50 days after sowing (DAS)." [Gramene:jcl, Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: penetrated root number
synonym: ['"npr (related)" RELATED []', '"number of penetrating roots (related)" RELATED []', '"PENRTNB (related)" RELATED []']

def: "A root system morphology trait (TO:0000985) which is the number of roots (PO:0009005) in a root system (PO:0025025)." [Gramene:jcl, Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, PATO:0001555, TO:cooperl, TO_GIT:357]
name: root number

comment: Leaf rolling is a feature observed in response to stresses like drought, water and temperature.  If you are annotating to this term, please add an additional annotation to vascular leaf morphology (TO:0000419) or non-vascular leaf morphology trait (TO:0000925), depending on the species.
def: "A leaf morphology trait (TO:0000748) which is the rolling of a leaf preceding the leaf drying stage." [Gramene:jcl, Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, TO:moorel]
name: leaf rolling

def: "Causal agent: Sarocladium oryzae. Symptoms: oblong or irregular brown to grey lesions on the leaf sheath near panicle; sometimes coalescing to prevent emergence of panicle." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: sheath rot disease resistance

comment: It is often associated with the accumulation of the aromatic compound 2-acetyl-1-pyrroline.
def: "The aroma of the cooked/uncooked grains." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: grain aroma trait

def: "Causal agent: rice yellow mottle virus (RYMV). Symptoms: stunting, reduced tillering, mottling and yellowish streaking of the leaves, delayed flowering or incomplete emergence of the panicle; in extreme cases, death of plants." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: rice yellow mottle virus resistance

def: "A panicle inflorescence morphology trait (TO:0000847) which is the mode of branching, angle of primary branches, and spikelet density of a panicle inflorescence (PO:0030123)." [IRRI:SES, TO:moorel]
name: panicle inflorescence type
synonym: ['"panicle attitude of branches (related)" RELATED []', '"PnT (related)" RELATED []', '"PNTYPE (related)" RELATED []']

def: "At 50 days after sowing (DAS), the thickness of roots penetrated through the wax-petrolatum layer is measured.  Penetrated root thickness is measured on penetrated roots immediately below the wax layer." [Gramene:jcl, Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: penetrated root thickness

def: "The ratio of deep root length (for the roots found 30cm below the soil surface) and the shoot length determined in a study." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: deep root to shoot ratio
synonym: ['"deep root length to shoot length ratio (related)" RELATED []', '"deep root ratio (related)" RELATED []', '"deep root/shoot ratio (related)" RELATED []', '"dr/s (related)" RELATED []', '"DRTSHRO (related)" RELATED []']

def: "The thickness of the root present 2cm below the soil surface." [Gramene:jcl, Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: basal root thickness

def: "Sensitivity to the osmoticum in the growth medium." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: osmotic response sensitivity

def: "Regeneration of the main stem and tillers after harvesting in a grass plant." [Gramene:jn, Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: ratooning ability

comment: It is a polysaccharide present in starch. Amylopectin is a polymer of alpha(1,4)-linked glucose units, as is amylose (see amylose). Unlike amylose, amylopectin contains branches of 2430 glucose units connected to the main chain by an alpha(1,6) linkage.
def: "Amount of amylopectin present in the plant or plant part." [ISBN:198506732]
name: amylopectin content

comment: If the endosperm has high amount of amylose it is called as non-glutinous endosperm. This is also an endosperm quality trait (TO:0000587).
def: "An endosperm morphology trait (TO:0000575) which is an opaque and hard endosperm (PO:0009089) with low or no amylose content (TO:0000196)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, PO:0009089, TO:moorel]
name: glutinous endosperm

comment: This is also an endosperm quality trait (TO:0000587).
def: "An endosperm morphology trait (TO:0000575) which is a wrinkled and glassy endosperm (PO:0009089) when dry." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, PO:0009089, TO:moorel]
name: sugary endosperm

comment: This is also an endosperm quality trait (TO:0000587). Refers to shrunken PATO:0000585 A decreased size quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting reduced size of a cell or constituent group of cells (for example, organ).
def: "An endosperm morphology trait (TO:0000575) which is a shrunken and opaque endosperm (PO:0009089)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, PO:0009089, TO:moorel]
name: shrunken endosperm

def: "A common sedge weed Monochoria vaginalis (monochoria), California arrowhead Sagittaria montevidensis, Gregg arrowhead Sagittaria longiloba, Ducksalad Heteranthera limosa, Echinodorus berteroi and E. cordifolius (Burhead), Ammannia spp (Redstems), Bacopa spp. (Water hyssops), Alisma plantago-aquatica (Common water plantain). Grows as a weed in the rice field. Can be distinguished from rice plant by the leaf shape, venation, stem cross-section and plant shape leaf shape." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, ISBN:9712200299, web:http//www.ipm.ucdavis.edu/PMG/r682700999.html]
name: broad-leaved weed

def: "Sensitivity to the phosphorus content in the growth medium. It is important in various biochemical pathways and storage of energy." [IRRI:SES]
name: phosphorus sensitivity

def: "The sensitivity response shown by the plant growing in a stagnant water for a long period of time (not unlike deepwater presence during flash flooding of the fields)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: deepwater stress

comment: This is also an endosperm quality trait (TO:0000587).
def: "An endosperm morphology trait (TO:0000575) which is an opaque and soft endosperm (PO:0009089)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, PO:0009089, TO:moorel]
name: floury endosperm

comment: This is also an endosperm quality trait (TO:0000587).
def: "An endosperm morphology trait (TO:0000575) which is a glassy and tarnished endosperm (PO:0009089) with low amylose content (TO:0000196)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, PO:0009089, TO:moorel]
name: dull endosperm

def: "Represents the different types of male sterility found in plants." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: male sterility type

def: "Assay for the amount of 13kDa seed storage protein present in the endosperm." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: endosperm storage protein-1 content

comment: The leaf shattering trait is the occurence of  the biological process of leaf abscission (GO:0060866): the controlled shedding of a leaf.
def: "A leaf growth and development trait (TO:0000655) which is the extent of leaf shattering based on the development of a leaf abscission zone (PO:0006501)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, PO:0006501, TO:cooperl]
name: leaf shattering

def: "Assay for amount of 57kDa seed storage protein present in the endosperm." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: endosperm storage protein-2 content

def: "Abortion of microspore development at uni-nucleate stage." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: wild abortive CMS

def: "The sterility induced by transgenes expressing cytotoxic component." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: genetically engineered male sterility

comment: It represents the damage done by the diease and/or the pathogen to the plant. The damage is a direct measure of resistance to the particular pathogen variety causing the disease.
def: "An assay to determine the resistance exhibited by a plant or a group of plants (population) in response to the disease caused by a pathogen infection as compared to the susceptible and/or the reference plants of the same species." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: disease resistance
synonym: ['"disease control (exact)" EXACT []', '"disease resistance trait (exact)" EXACT []', '"disease susceptibility (narrow)" NARROW []', '"disease tolerance (exact)" EXACT []']

def: "An embryo shape trait (TO:0000193) that is a large sized plant embryo (PO:0009009)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, PO:0009009, TO:moorel]
name: giant embryo

def: "Determined as the dry mass of roots per unit soil volume at a given soil section." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: root mass density

def: "Root mass density 0-15 cm was calculated as the dry mass of roots per unit soil volume at 0-15 cm soil section." [Gramene:jcl, Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: root mass density 0-15

def: "Since there is no genetic resistance to rats, the damage can be quantified as it does not represent resistance." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: rat damage resistance

def: "Root mass density 15-30 cm was calculated as the dry mass of roots per unit soil volume at 15-30 cm soil section." [Gramene:jcl, Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: root mass density 15-30

def: "Root mass density 30-45 cm was calculated as the dry mass of roots per unit soil volume at 30-45 cm soil section." [Gramene:jcl, Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: root mass density 30-45

def: "Calculated as percent of root mass density over the total root mass density. Both parameters scored at the same depth." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: percent root mass density

comment: Evaluated at growth stage:6-7 in rice.
def: "Causal agent: the stem nematode Dictylenchus angustus. Symptoms: leaf mottling or chlorotic discoloration in a splash pattern at base of young leaves in stem elongation or mid-tillering stage; brown stains may develop on leaves and sheaths which later intensify to a dark brown color. A characteristic distortion consisting of twisting and withering of young leaves. A distortion of panicle which either remains enclosed with in a swollen sheath, partially emerge but are twisted and with unfilled grains or emerge completely but with unfilled grains and resembling a whitehead." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: ufra damage

def: "Calculated as percent of root mass density in this section over the total root mass density. Both scored at the 0-15cm depth." [Gramene:jcl, Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: percent root mass density 0-15

def: "Calculated as percent of root mass density in this section over the total root mass density. Both scored at the 15-30cm depth." [Gramene:jcl, Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: percent root mass density 15-30

def: "A flag leaf morphology trait (TO:0000832) which is an angle of the flag leaf (PO:0020103) measured near the collar, as the angle of attachment between the flag leaf blade and the main inflorescence axis in grass plants." [IRRI:SES, PO:0020103, TO:cooperl, TO:moorel]
name: flag leaf angle

def: "Calculated as percent of root mass density in this section over the total root mass density. Both scored at the 30-45cm depth." [Gramene:jcl, Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: percent root mass density 30-45

def: "Causal agent: rice grassy stunt virus 2 (RGSV2). Symptoms: RGSV2 causes severe stunting, excessive tillering, yellow to orange and narrow leaves with small rusty spots." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: rice grassy stunt virus-2 resistance

def: "Causal agent: rice grassy stunt virus 1 (RGSV1). Symptoms: RGSV1 causes severe stunting, excessive tillering, pale green to yellow and narrow leaves with small rusty spots." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: rice grassy stunt virus-1 resistance

def: "Proportion of usable (economically significant) biomass over total (biological) biomass, expressed as a percentage." [Gramene:jcl, Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: harvest index

def: "Causal agent: Ustilaginoidea virens. Symptoms: infected grains are transformed into yellow-greenish or greenish-black velvety-looking spore balls." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: false smut disease resistance

def: "Sensitivity to the far red light content in the growth environment." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: far red light sensitivity

def: "Water potential of a leaf." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: leaf water potential

def: "Actual measurements in millimeters from the outer diameter of the stem at the basal portion of the main stem." [IRRI:SES]
name: basal internode diameter

def: "Is an indirect measure of gelatinization temperature. Observed by placing six milled-rice kernels in 10ml 1.7% KOH in a shallow container and arrange them so that they do not touch. Let them stand for 23hrs at 30degC temperature and score for spreading. Measure for Alkali digestion is inversely proportional to the gelatinization temperature, e.g. if alkali digestion is low, the gelatinization temperature is high." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: alkali digestion

comment: Actual measurements, in centimeters of the leaf. Refers to length (PATO:0000122): A 1-D extent quality which is equal to the distance between two points. In maize, this is measured in centimeters. If you are annotating to this term, please add an additional annotation to vascular leaf morphology (TO:0000419) or non-vascular leaf morphology trait (TO:0000925), depending on the species.
def: "A leaf size (TO:0002637) trait which is a length of a leaf (PO:0025034)." [IRRI:SES, PO:0025034, TO:cooperl, TO:moorel]
name: leaf length

def: "Leaf relative water content is determined at midday (12.00 noon)." [Gramene:jcl, Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: leaf relative water content
synonym: ['"leaf relative water content (related)" RELATED []', '"rec (related)" RELATED []', '"RELWCN (related)" RELATED []']

comment: Often determined when the 50% length of the inflorescence has emerged as compared to its full length. Number of days is calculated from either the day of sowing of seeds or from the day of transplanting the seedlings (in case of rice) depending on type of study.
def: "Number of days required for the inflorescence (head/cob/panicle) to emerge from the flag leaf of a plant or a group of plants in a study." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: days to heading

def: "Total protein content of the brown rice." [IRRI:SES]
name: brown rice protein
synonym: ['"brown rice protein content (related)" RELATED []', '"BrP (related)" RELATED []', '"BRWRPROT (related)" RELATED []', '"Prt (related)" RELATED []']

def: "A cardinal organ part morphology trait (TO:0000754) which is the color of a lemma apiculus (PO:0025616)." [IRRI:SES]
name: lemma apiculus color

comment: Refer to color PATO:0000014: A composite chromatic quality composed of hue, saturation and intensity parts.
def: "An awn morphology trait (TO:0002718) which is a color of the awn (PO:0025349)." [IRRI:SES, PO:0025349, TO:moorel]
name: awn color

def: "An inflorescence branching (TO:0000050) trait which is the extent of secondary branching that usually determines the shape and compactness of the inflorescence  (PO:0009049) (such as in rice panicle)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES, PO:0009049, TO:moorel]
name: secondary branching of inflorescence
synonym: ['"panicle secondary branching (related)" RELATED []', '"PnBr (related)" RELATED []', '"SBR (related)" RELATED []', '"secondary branching of panicle (related)" RELATED []']

def: "Relative yield was calculated as the ratio of biomass in stress to that of control." [Gramene:jcl, Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: relative biomass

comment: Milling is part of rice processing where the caryopsis hull (PO:0006000) and bran is removed. Milled rice consists of the broken kernels as well as the head rice (whole or 3/4 of original length or longer) milled kernels.
def: "A grain yield trait (TO:0000396) which is the proportion of kernels remaining after milling to remove the bran." [RiceCAP https://ricecap.hosted.uark.edu/glossary_ricecaplist.htm#M]
name: milled rice yield

def: "A shoot axis internode morphology trait (TO:0000755) which is the length of a shoot axis internode (PO:0005005)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: shoot axis internode length

comment: Seed length is a component of seed size (TO:0000391) and has a component of seed quality (TO:0000162). Refer to length (PATO:0000122): A 1-D extent quality which is equal to the distance between two points.
def: "A seed morphology trait (TO:0000184) which is the length of a seed (PO:0009010)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES, PO:0009010, TO:moorel]
name: seed length

def: "Causal agent: rice hoja blanca virus (RHBV). Symptoms: cream colored to yellow spots, elongating and coalescing to form longitudinal yellowish green to pale green striations. Streaks may coalesce to cover the whole leaf. Brown and sterile glumes with typical \"parrot beak\" shape of deformation." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: rice hoja blanca disease resistance

comment: It represents the damage done by the diease and/or the viral pathogen to the plant. The damage is a direct measure of resistance to the particular viral strain causing the diease.
def: "An assay to determine the resistance exhibited by a plant or a group of plants (population) in response to the disease caused by a viral pathogen infection as compared to the susceptible and/or the reference plants of the same species." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: viral disease resistance

comment: Seed width is measured in millimeters as the distance across the seed and is a component of the seed size (TO:0000391) and can be a component of seed quality (TO:0000162). Refers to (PATO:0000921): A 1-D extent quality which is equal to the distance from one side of an object to another side which is opposite.
def: "A seed morphology trait (TO:0000184) which is the width of a seed (PO:0009010)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES, PO:0009010, TO:moorel]
name: seed width

def: "Causal agent: Pelopidas mathias (Fabricius) and Parnara guttata." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: rice skipper resistance

def: "A panicle morphology trait (TO:0000847) which is the average number of panicles per plant in a study." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, TO:moorel]
name: panicle number
synonym: ['"NOP (related)" RELATED []', '"NP (related)" RELATED []', '"number of effective tiller per plant (related)" RELATED []', '"number of panicle (related)" RELATED []', '"panicle number per plant (related)" RELATED []', '"panicle number per tiller (related)" RELATED []', '"PN (related)" RELATED []', '"PNNB (related)" RELATED []', '"seed setting tillers per plant (related)" RELATED []', '"spike number (related)" RELATED []', '"TP (related)" RELATED []']

def: "Relative yield is calculated as a ratio of yield in stress to that of control." [Gramene:jcl, Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: relative yield

def: "Causal agent: Stenchaetothrips biformis. monitored at growth stage 2-3." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: thrips resistance

def: "The index is calculated as, DSI = (1-Yds/Yns), where Yds and Yns are mean yields of a given genotype in drought susceptible (DS) and non-susceptible (NS) environments respectively." [Gramene:jcl, Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: drought susceptibility index
synonym: ['"drought score (related)" RELATED []', '"drought sensitivity index (related)" RELATED []', '"DRSID (related)" RELATED []', '"DRSSID (related)" RELATED []', '"DSI (related)" RELATED []']

def: "At 50 days after sowing (DAS), the dry weight of roots penetrated through the wax-petrolatum layer is measured." [Gramene:jcl, Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: penetrated root dry weight

def: "Assay determines temperature of the leaf canopy." [Gramene:jcl, Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: canopy temperature

def: "Sensitivity to the red light content in the growth environment." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: red light sensitivity

def: "Sensitivity response observed in an environment illuminated with blue light." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: blue light sensitivity

def: "Response shown by the plant in the presence of UV light stress." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: UV light sensitivity
synonym: ['"Ultraviolet light sensitivity (related)" RELATED []', '"Ultraviolet resistance (related)" RELATED []', '"UV resistance (related)" RELATED []', '"UVRS (related)" RELATED []']

def: "Response shown by the plant in terms of sensitivity to one or more types of radiation stress (quality and quantity of light)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: radiation response trait
synonym: ['"radiation sensitivity (related)" RELATED []', '"RADSN (related)" RELATED []', '"response to radiation (related)" RELATED []']

def: "A fruit quality trait (TO:0002728) that is the commercial and /or economical value of the grain (i.e. fruit (PO:0009001)), or its overall improvement." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, TO:cooperl]
name: grain quality trait

comment: The most important auxin produced by plants is indole-3-acetic acid (IAA).
def: "Response with respect to application of auxin." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: auxin sensitivity
synonym: ['"AUXSN (related)" RELATED []', '"IAA response (related)" RELATED []', '"IAA sensitivity (related)" RELATED []', '"indole-3-acetic acid response (related)" RELATED []', '"indole-3-acetic acid sensitivity (related)" RELATED []']

def: "Response by the plant in terms of resistivity or sensitivity to either the biotic or the abiotic types of stress." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: stress trait
synonym: ['"crop damage (related)" RELATED []', '"stress resistance (related)" RELATED []', '"stress susceptibility (related)" RELATED []', '"stress tolerance (related)" RELATED []']

def: "A panicle inflorescence morphology trait (TO:0000847) which is the extent of coverage of panicle inflorescence (PO:0030123) by a sheath of a flag leaf (PO:0020103)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: panicle inflorescence exsertion

def: "Sensitivity to the gibberellic acid content in the growth medium or on external application." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: gibberellic acid sensitivity
synonym: ['"GA3 response (related)" RELATED []', '"GASN (related)" RELATED []', '"GB response (related)" RELATED []', '"gibberellic acid response (related)" RELATED []', '"Gibberellin response (related)" RELATED []']

def: "Sensitivity to the cytokinin content in the growth medium or external application." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: cytokinin sensitivity

def: "Response by the plant in terms of resistivity or sensitivity to abiotic stress." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: abiotic stress trait

def: "Abortion of microspore development at trinucleate stage." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: chinsurah boro CMS

def: "Some plants can elongate and grow in areas annually flooded to varying depths. The scale is based on the performance of check varieties. Specify water depth under which the data was recorded." [IRRI:SES]
name: elongation ability

def: "Sensitivity to the jasmonic acid content in the growth medium or on external application." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: jasmonic acid sensitivity

def: "Sensitivity to ethylene (C2H2) content in the growth medium or the environment." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: ethylene sensitivity

comment: Symptoms: lesions usually start near the leaf tips or leaf margins or both, and extend down the outer edge(s). Young lesions are pale to grayish green, later turning yellow to grey (dead) with time. In very susceptible varieties, lesions may extend to the entire leaf length into the leaf sheath. Young leaves should not be inoculated for assay. Old or leaves with symptoms of nutrient deficiency or other diseases should also be avoided for inoculation.
def: "Causal agent: Xanthomonas oryzae pv. oryzae." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: rice bacterial blight disease resistance

def: "A nutrient sensitivity (TO:0000480) response shown by the plant grown in either an excess or deficient amount of the macronutrient in the growth medium." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: macronutrient sensitivity

comment: It is expected that the herbicide application must not affect the agronomic yield, if any.
def: "An assay to determine the tolerance exhibited by a plant or a group of plants (population) towards the applied herbicide 2,4-dichlorophenoxyacetic acid (2,4 D)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: 2,4-dichlorophenoxyacetic acid sensitivity

def: "Plant sensitivity to soils with acidic conditions (pH<7)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, TO:moorel]
name: acid soil sensitivity

def: "Response by the plant in terms of resistivity or sensitivity to biotic stress." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: biotic stress trait

comment: Determined by percent of spikelets with grains identified by pressing the spikelets with the fingers and counting those that have no grains or the percent seed setting.\nRefer to fertility (PATO:0000274): A reproductive quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's initiating, sustaining, or supporting reproduction.
def: "A spikelet morphology trait (TO:0000657) which is the fertility to a spikelet (PO:0009051)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES, PO:0009051, TO:moorel]
name: spikelet fertility
synonym: ['"percent sterility (related)" RELATED []', '"seed setting (related)" RELATED []', '"SpFert (related)" RELATED []', '"SPKFRT (related)" RELATED []']

comment: Seed weight is a component of seed yield (TO:0000905) and seed quality (TO:0000162). Refer to weight (PATO:0000128): A physical quality inhering in a bearer that has mass near a gravitational body.
def: "A seed morphology trait (TO:0000184) which is the weight of a seed (PO:0009010)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, PO:0009010, TO:moorel]
name: seed weight

def: "The tolerance exhibited by a plant or a group of plants (population) towards the applied insecticide." [TO:moorel]
name: insecticide sensitivity

def: "The trait instances, which either cannot be assigned any of the eight top level parent terms such as biochemical, anatomy, development quality, stature/vigor, sterility/fertility, stress and the yield or are yet to be assigned a parent." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: other miscellaneous trait

def: "A multi-tissue plant structure morphology trait (TO:0000836) which is a seed (PO:0009010)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, PO:0009010, TO:moorel]
name: seed morphology trait

def: "Color of the stigma in a blossoming flower." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: stigma color

def: "An anther morphology trait (TO:1000022) which is the color (PATO:0000014) of an anther (PO:0009066)" [TO:austin_meier]
name: anther color

def: "Drought sensitivity is highly interactive with crop phenology, plant growth prior to stress, and timing, duration, and intensity of drought stress. For many soils, it takes at least 2 rainless weeks to cause marked differences in drought sensitivity during the vegetative stage and at least 7 rainless days during the reproductive stage to cause severe drought injury. Leaf rolling precedes leaf drying during drought. Repeated ratings are recommended through progress of the drought." [IRRI:SES]
name: drought sensitivity

def: "An embryo morphology trait (TO:0000064) which is the absence of embryo in the developing seed." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, TO:moorel]
name: embryoless

comment: Refer to color PATO:0000014: A composite chromatic quality composed of hue, saturation and intensity parts.
def: "A seed coat morphology trait (TO:0000838) which is the color of the seed coat (PO:0009088)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES, PO:0009088, TO:moorel]
name: seed coat color

def: "Causal agent: Dicladispa armigera." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: rice hispa resistance

def: "Causal agent: Cnaphalocrocis medinalis." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: leaf-roller resistance

comment: Refer to shape PATO:0000052:A morphological quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's ratios of distances between its features (points, edges, surfaces and also holes etc).
def: "An embryo morphology trait (TO:0000064) which is the shape of a plant embryo (PO:0009009)." [PO:0009009, TO:moorel]
name: embryo shape

comment: Refer to globular (PATO:0001499): A spheroid quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's resembling a ball (a sphere whose equatorial diameter is equal to the polar diameter).
def: "An embryo shape trait (TO:0000193) which is a globular plant embryo (PO:0009009)." [PO:0009009, TO:moorel]
name: globular embryo

def: "A plant embryo morphology trait (TO:0000064) which is an embryo of the germinating seed not producing a shoot." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, TO:moorel]
name: shootless embryo

comment: Amylose is a helical polymer made of α-D-glucose units, bound to each other through α(1→4) glycosidic bonds. This polysaccharide is one of the two components of starch, making up approximately 20-30% of the structure. The other component is amylopectin, which makes up 70–80% of the structure. (REF: Wikipedia)
def: "A polysaccharide content trait (TO:0006007) which is the amount of amylose (CHEBI:28102) in a plant structure (PO:0009011)." [IRRI:SES, ISBN:198506732]
name: amylose content

comment: Refer to color (PATO:0000014): A composite chromatic quality composed of hue, saturation and intensity parts.
def: "A ligule morphology trait (TO:0002748) which is the color of a ligule (PO:0020105)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES, PO:0020105, TO:cooperl]
name: ligule color

def: "Absence of roots in the seedling or plant." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: rootless

def: "A measure of brittleness of the stem of a grass plant." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: brittle culm

comment: Refer to color PATO:0000014: A composite chromatic quality composed of hue, saturation and intensity parts.
def: "A panicle inflorescence morphology trait (TO:0000847) which is the variation in color of the panicle inflorescence (PO:0030123)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: panicle inflorescence color

def: "Ratio of germinated to non-germinated seeds." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: germination ratio

comment: Symptoms: linear lesions with small bacterial exudates evident. This scale may also be used for leaf smut caused by Entyloma oryzae.
def: "Causal agent: Xanthomonas oryzae pv. oryzicola." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: rice bacterial leaf streak disease resistance

comment: Symptoms: lesions usually start near the leaf tips or leaf margins or both, and extend down the outer edge(s). Young lesions are pale to grayish green, later turning yellow to grey (dead) with time. In very susceptible varieties, lesions may extend to the entire leaf length into the leaf sheath. Kresek or seedling blight causes wilting and death of plant.
def: "Causal agent: Xanthomonas oryzae pv. oryzae." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: rice seedling blight disease resistance

def: "Causal agent: Sagotella furcifera. Symptoms: partial to pronounced yellowing and increasing severity of stunting. Extreme signs are wilting and death of plants. Infested areas in the field may be patchy. (similar to the symptoms of whitebacked planthopper)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: white-backed planthopper resistance

comment: In rice, it is measured against the culm on the leaf below the flag leaf. Refer to angle value (PATO:0000602).
def: "A leaf attitude (TO:0000206) which is  the angle of a leaf (PO:0025034) measured against the stem." [IRRI:SES, TO:cooperl]
name: leaf angle

comment: Comment: Refers to: height (PATO_0000119): A 1-D extent quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's vertical dimension of extension.
def: "A whole plant morphology trait (TO:0000398) which is the height of a whole plant (PO:0000003)." [IRRI:SES, PO:0000003, TO:cooperl]
name: plant height

def: "A spikelet floret morphology trait (TO:0000274) which is the number of lemma (PO:0009037) in a spikelet floret (PO:0009082)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, PATO:0001555, PO:0009037, PO:0009082, TO:cooperl, TO:moorel]
name: lemma number

def: "A spikelet floret morphology trait (TO:0000274) which is the number of  palea (PO:0009038) in a spikelet floret (PO:0009082)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, PATO:0001555, PO:0009038, PO:0009082, TO:cooperl, TO:moorel]
name: palea number

def: "A stamen morphology trait (TO:0000215) which is the number of anthers (PO:0009066) in a stamen (PO:0009029)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, TO:cooperl]
name: anther number

def: "Scored by gel consistency type in mm." [IRRI:SES]
name: gel consistency

def: "Causal agent: Nephotettix spp. (Nephotettix virescens and Nephotettix cincticeps). It is the major vector for transmitting the tungro virus disease. Symptoms: Partial to pronounced yellowing and increasing severity of stunting. Extreme signs are wilting to death of plants. Infected areas in the field may be patchy." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: green leafhopper resistance

def: "Causal agent: rice grassy stunt virus 1 (RGSV1) and rice grassy stunt virus 2 (RGSV2). Symptoms: RGSV1 causes severe stunting, excessive tillering, pale green to yellow and narrow leaves with small rusty spots. RGSV2 causes severe stunting, excessive tillering, yellow to orange and narrow leaves with small rusty spots." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: rice grassy stunt 1 and 2 virus resistance

comment: Refers to shape (PATO:0000052): A morphological quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's ratios of distances between its features (points, edges, surfaces and also holes etc).
def: "An anther morphology trait (TO:1000022) which is the shape (PATO:0000052) of an anther (PO:0009066)." [TO:ethan_johnson]
name: anther shape

def: "A microsporophyll morphology trait (TO:0000868) which is a quality of a stamen (PO:0009029)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, PO:0009029, TO:moorel]
name: stamen morphology trait

def: "Male sterility affected by both temperature and photoperiod." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: genic male sterility-thermo-photoperiod sensitive
synonym: ['"thermo-photoperiod sensitive genic male sterility (related)" RELATED []', '"TPGMS (related)" RELATED []']

def: "Observations are made on staining behavior and number of nuclei in most of the pollen." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: pollen abortion type
synonym: ['"abortion pattern (related)" RELATED []', '"abortion pattern of male sterile lines (related)" RELATED []']

def: "Causal agent: Leptocorisa oratorius. Monitored at growth stage 7-9, resistance is a measure of damaged grains per panicle." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: rice bug resistance

comment: Refer to color (PATO:0000014): A composite chromatic quality composed of hue, saturation and intensity parts.
def: "A glume morphology trait (TO:0000869) which is the color of a glume (PO:0009039)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, PO:0009039, TO:moorel]
name: glume color
synonym: ['"GLCL (related)" RELATED []', '"glume discoloration (related)" RELATED []', '"glume pigmentation (related)" RELATED []', '"pigmentation of glume (related)" RELATED []']

comment: Depending on the grain type, whole milled kernels are spearated using special sized screens. The weight of whole milled kernels or head rice is expressed as a percentage of the original rough rice sample.
def: "A grain yield trait (TO:0000396) which is the amount of whole (3/4 of original length or longer) milled kernels separated from the total amount of milled rice." [https://ricecap.hosted.uark.edu/glossary_ricecaplist.htm#H, TO:cooperl]
name: head rice yield
synonym: ['"head milled rice (related)" RELATED []', '"head rice ratio (related)" RELATED []', '"HEADR (related)" RELATED []']

def: "A carpel morphology trait (TO:0006012) which is a quality of a pistil." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, TO:moorel]
name: pistil morphology trait

def: "Sensitivity to the iron ion content in the growth medium. It is important for synthesis of chlorophyll and some enzyme activities." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]

def: "An androecium morphology trait (TO:0000215) which is the number of stamens (PO:0009029) present in an androecium (PO:0009061)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, PO:0009029, PO:0009049, TO:austin_meier, TO:moorel]
name: stamen number

def: "A measure of either the absence of auricle or the length of auricle being zero." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: auricleless

comment: refer to PATO:0000122- A 1-D extent quality which is equal to the distance between two points.
def: "A root morphology trait (TO:0000043) which is the length of a root (PO:0009005)." [Gramene:jcl\nGR\:pj, TO:austin_meier\nTO\:cooperl]
name: root length
synonym: ['"maximum root depth (related)" RELATED []', '"maximum root length (related)" RELATED []', '"MRD (related)" RELATED []', '"MRL (related)" RELATED []', '"RTLG (related)" RELATED []']

def: "Sensitivity response on the plant development and the related growth stages by the duration of light, to which the plant has been exposed." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: photoperiod sensitivity trait

def: "Absence of crown roots in the plant." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: crown rootless

comment: This is also an endosperm quality trait (TO:0000587).
def: "An endosperm morphology trait (TO:0000575) which is the absence of endosperm (PO:0009089) in the seed (PO:0009010) or grain." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, PO:0009010, PO:0009089, TO:moorel]
name: endospermless

def: "Caused by the interaction of cytoplasmic (mitochondrial) and nuclear genomes. The trait shows non-mendelian inheritance or maternal inheritance." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: rice cytoplasmic male sterility

comment: Root volume is an indirect measure of root mass or density and can be quantified by water displacement method, in cubic centimeters.
def: "A root morphology trait (TO:0000043) which is the volume of a root (PO:0009005)." [GR_REF:6917, Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: root volume

def: "The embryo of the germinating seed does not produce roots." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: radicleless

comment: Refer to absent (PATO:0000462): A quality denoting the lack of an entity.
def: "A ligule morphology trait (TO:0002748) which is the absence of a ligule (PO:0020105)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, PO:0020105, TO:cooperl]
name: liguleless

def: "Response by the plant in terms of sensitivity to water stress (quality and quantity of water)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: water stress trait

def: "A chemical stress sensitivity (TO:0000238) which is the response by the plant to a specific growth medium." [TO:moorel]

comment: The worms appear suddenly in masses and move like an army from field to field so that seedbeds or the direct seeded fields look as if grazed by cattles. Generally, a transplanted crop is not severely affected. Damage by armyworms is most serious during periods of stem elongation and grain formation. Larvae defoliate plants, typically by chewing angular pieces off leaves. They may also feed on the panicle near the developing kernels causing these kernels to dry before filling. This feeding causes all or parts of the panicle to  turn white. If the entire panicle is white, the damage may also be due to stem rot or feeding by rats. The  seriousness of armyworm injury depends on the maturity of the plant and the amount of tissue consumed. Significant yield reduction can occur if defoliation is greater than 25% at 2 to 3 weeks before heading. They migrate from field to field and extensive losses are often caused within a week. Their migration is facilitated by the absence of standing water in the field.
def: "Causal agent: Pseudaletia unipuncta, Spodoptera mauritia and Spodoptera praefica. The swarming caterpillars cause severe damage to rice plants in nursery beds." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, web:http//pne.gsnu.ac.kr/riceipm/spodopte.htm, web:http//www.ipm.ucdavis.edu/PMG/r682300411.html]
name: armyworm resistance

[Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, ISBN:9712200299, www:http//www.ipm.ucdavis.edu/PMG/r682700999.html]
name: grass weed

comment: Often determinded by either pollen shedding, exsertion of the anthers or simply opening of the flower.
def: "A flowering time trait (TO:0002616) which is the number of days required for an individual flower (PO:0009046), a whole plant (PO:0000003) or a plant population to reach flowering stage (PO:0007616) from a predetermined time point (e.g. the date of seed sowing, seedling transplant, or seedling emergence)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, TO:cooperl]
name: days to flowering trait
synonym: ['"days to flowering (exact)" EXACT []', '"Delay in flowering time (narrow)" NARROW []', '"DTFL (related)" RELATED []']

def: "Number of tillers per plant, should represent most plants within a study." [IRRI:SES]
name: tiller number

def: "Weeds reduce the yield regardless of planting season. They compete for sunlight, nutrients and water. If any of these is lacking, the others cannot be used effectively, even if a lot are present. Thus, the competition results in poor plant growth and less yield." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, ISBN:9712200299]
name: weed damage

def: "Causal agent: Sogatodes orizicola (Muir), Sagotella furcifera and Sogatodes cubanus. Sogatodes orizicola is also a vector for the Rice black streaked dwarf fijivirus and rice hoja blanca  virus (RHBV)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: sogatodes resistance

def: "Abortion of microspore development at bi-nucleate stage." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: cms-hl type

def: "Sensitivity to the zinc content in the growth medium. It acts as cofactor for certain enzymes like Class II aldolases, metalloproteases, alkaline phosphatase, etc." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: zinc sensitivity

def: "The dry weight of the whole plant." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal37]
name: plant dry weight
synonym: ['"DMASS (related)" RELATED []', '"dry mass (related)" RELATED []', '"PTDWT (related)" RELATED []', '"RTWT (related)" RELATED []', '"total dry mass (related)" RELATED []']

def: "Abortion at later stage of microspore development, the pollen looks like fertile pollen." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: aborted at pollen maturity stage

def: "Sensitivity to aluminum content in the growth media." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: aluminum sensitivity

def: "Exceptional vigor of growth etc. in plants or in animal, resulting from cross breeding among inter or intra species." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: heterosis
synonym: ['"HET (related)" RELATED []', '"heterosis in f1 hybrid (related)" RELATED []', '"hybrid vigor (related)" RELATED []']

def: "Causal agent: Cochliobolus miyabeanus (Bipolaris oryzae, Drechslera oryzae). Symptom: typical leaf spots are small, oval or circular and dark brown. Larger lesions usually have same color on the edges but have a pale (usually grayish) center. Most spots have a light yellow halo around the outer edge." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: brown spot disease resistance

comment: Growth and development traits are qualities of the development of the whole plant or plant parts.
def: "A plant trait (TO:0000387) which is the growth (GO:0048590) and development (GO:0032502) of a plant anatomical entity (PO:0025131) or a constituent cellular component (GO:0005575)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, TO:cooperl]
name: plant growth and development trait

comment: Ofetn influenced by the environemnt that includes, day light, temperature and geographic location.
def: "A flowering time trait which is the timing of the flowering (anthesis) of female flowers." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: female flowering
synonym: ['"days to silk (related)" RELATED []', '"DTSLK (related)" RELATED []', '"Female flower anthesis (related)" RELATED []', '"Female flower flowering (related)" RELATED []', '"FEMFLW (related)" RELATED []', '"FFLW (related)" RELATED []']

def: "Measure of growth or elongation rate of the leaf in a plant." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: leaf elongation rate

def: "A shoot axis morphology trait (TO:0000739) which is the quality of a stem (PO:0009047)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, PO:0009047, TO:moorel]
name: stem morphology trait

def: "Changes monitored in leaf collar color." [IRRI:SES]
name: leaf collar color

comment: Often influenced by the environment that includes, daylight, temperature and geographic location.
def: "A flowering time trait (TO:0002616) which is the timing of the flowering (anthesis) of male flowers." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: male flowering
synonym: ['"male flower anthesis (related)" RELATED []', '"male flower flowering (related)" RELATED []', '"MALEFLW (related)" RELATED []', '"MFLW (related)" RELATED []']

def: "Measure of time taken by the reproductive growth phase in a plant's life cycle." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: reproductive growth time

def: "The changes in the color of basal leaf sheath." [IRRI:SES]
name: basal leaf sheath color

def: "Measure of the vegetative growth phase time in a plant's life cycle." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: vegetative growth time

comment: Actual measurements, in centimeters of the widest portion of the leaf. To be precise use the children terms leaf lamina width (TO:0002720) or  'leaf sheath width (TO:0002721). Refers to width (PATO:0000921) A 1-D extent quality which is equal to the distance from one side of an object to another side which is opposite. If you are annotating to this term, please add an additional annotation to vascular leaf morphology (TO:0000419) or non-vascular leaf morphology trait (TO:0000925), depending on the species.
def: "A leaf size (TO:0002637) trait which the width of a leaf (PO:0025034)." [IRRI:SES, PO:0025034, TO:cooperl, TO:moorel]
name: leaf width

def: "A plant trait (TO:0000387) which is a harvestable product that is a plant anatomical entity (PO:0025131) or one or more constituent cellular components (GO:0005575) contained therein." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, TO:cooperl]
name: yield trait

def: "Ratio of amount of amylose to amylopectin content." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: amylose to amylopectin ratio

def: "A reproductive shoot system morphology trait (TO:0000786) that is a quality of an inflorescence (PO:0009049)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, PO:0009049]
name: inflorescence morphology trait
synonym: ['"Head morphology trait (narrow)" NARROW []', '"inflorescence structure trait (related)" RELATED []']

comment: Breakdown is usually associated with the tendency of gelatinized starch granules to break during holding at high temperature, accompanied with continuous shearing (Han and Hamaker 2001). Breakdown is usually calculated from a resulting viscogram by subtracting trough from peak viscosity. The increase in rice flour breakdown viscosity, although not always significant (P < 0.05), suggests a greater protection of the starch granule integrity. This probably is due to the increased affinity of proteins to interact with starch, as a result of protein denaturation. The resulting formation of protein–starch complexes tends to increase rice flour peak viscosity.
def: "A cooking quality trait that is the tendency of gelatinized starch granules to break during cooking, especially at high temperature." [PMCID:PMC434838, TO:cooperl]
name: breakdown viscosity

comment: Refer to width PATO:0000921: A 1-D extent quality which is equal to the distance from one side of an object to another side which is opposite. Refer to length (PATO:0000122): A 1-D extent quality which is equal to the distance between two points. Refer to size (PATO:0000117): A morphology quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's physical magnitude. Size categories ranging from small to medium to large.
def: "A grain length to width ratio (TO:0002731) which is determined from grain length and grain width on dehulled unpolished rice grain." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, TO:moorel]
name: brown rice length to width ratio
synonym: ['"brown rice length to width ratio (related)" RELATED []', '"BRWRRO (related)" RELATED []']

def: "Causal agent: Monographella albescens (Microdochium oryzae). Symptoms: the lesions occurs mostly near leaf tips, but sometimes start at the margin of the blade and develops into large ellipsoid areas encircled by dark-brown, narrow bands accompanied by a light-brown halo." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: leaf scald disease resistance

def: "The percentage of cracked dehulled grain with most of the size still intact." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: cracked grain percentage

comment: Thousand grain weights are measured in grams on a precision balance on 100 well-developed whole grains (with the caryopsis hull; PO:0006000), dried to 13% moisture content.
def: "A grain weight (TO:0000919) which is the weight of a sample of 1000 grains (caryopsis fruit; PO:0030104), with the caryopsis hull (PO:0006000)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: 1000-grain weight
synonym: ['"1000-grain weight (exact)" EXACT []', '"TGRWT (exact)" EXACT []', '"thousand grain weight (exact)" EXACT []', '"thousand seed weight (related)" RELATED []', '"TSDWT (related)" RELATED []']

def: "Percentage opaque white area in the kernel belly." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: grain belly percent white

def: "An assay to determine the resistance exhibited by a plant or a group of plants (population) in response to nematode infestation as compared to the susceptible and/or the reference plants of the same species." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: nematode damage resistance

comment: For color of the dehulled grain, see pericarp color (TO:0000707).  Refer to color PATO:0000014: A composite chromatic quality composed of hue, saturation and intensity parts.
def: "A fruit color (TO:0002617) trait which is the color of dehulled, milled grain, which does not have pericarp (PO:0009084)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, PO:0009084, TO:moorel]
name: milled grain color

def: "Causal agent: rice ragged stunt virus (RRSV). Symptoms: plants are stunted but remain dark green. Leaves are ragged and twisted. Vein swelling on leaf collar, leaf blades and leaf sheaths." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal\,, IRRI:SES]
name: rice ragged stunt virus resistance

comment: This includes physiological, molecular and biochemical traits as well.
def: "A measurable or observable characteristic of a cellular component (GO:0005575), biological process (GO:0008150) or molecular function (GO:0003674) that is part of, or has participant a plant anatomical entity (PO:0025131) and/or a plant structure development stage (PO:0009012)." [GO:0003674, GO:0005575, GO:0008150, Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, PO:0009012, PO:0025131, TO:cooperl]
name: plant trait

def: "Yield of forage matter upon harvest." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: forage yield

def: "Shows mendelian inheritance, caused by genetic modifications or mutations in the nuclear genome." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: nuclear mediated male sterility

def: "Percentage opaque white area in the kernel core." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: grain core percent white

comment: Seed size is determined by the ratio of the seed length to seed width and is a component of seed quality (TO:0000162).  Seed size may be a qualitative measure or may be organized into categories ranging from small to medium to large.  Refers to size (PATO:0000117): A morphology quality  inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's physical magnitude.
def: "A seed morphology trait (TO:0000184) which is the size of a seed (PO:0009010)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, PO:0009010, TO:cooperl]
name: seed size

def: " A plant trait (TO:0000387) which is a measure of either the fertility or sterility, contributed by nonfunctional male and or female plant parts or their incompatible interaction. This also includes traits on seed setting behavior in the fruit (caryopsis) of a grass plant that can be assayed in terms of spikelet sterility or fertility." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: sterility or fertility trait

def: "Response by the plant in terms of sensitivity to sufficiently prolonged water deficit/scarcity or scanty water content in the soil or growth medium, that can cause damage to the plant." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: drought related trait

comment: In rice, the grain yield is often measured in kilograms per hectare at 14 percent moisture, if the experiment was done on a field trial.
def: "A fruit yield trait (TO:0000871) that is the amount of grain." [IRRI:SES, TO:contributors, TO:cooperl]
name: grain yield trait

comment: Refer to size (PATO:0000117): A morphology quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's physical magnitude. Size categories ranging from small to medium to large.
def: "A fruit size (TO:0002625) which is the size of a dehulled, milled grain without pericarp (PO:0009084)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, PO:0009084, TO:moorel]
name: grain size

def: "A plant structure morphology trait (TO:0000839) which is a quality of a whole plant (PO:0000003)." [PO:0000003, TO:cooperl]
name: whole plant morphology trait

def: "A grain quality trait (TO:0000399) which is the thickness of a dehulled grain with a pericarp (PO:0009084)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, PO:0009084, TO:moorel]
name: grain thickness

comment: Refer to color PATO:0000014: A composite chromatic quality composed of hue, saturation and intensity parts.
def: "A lemma morphology trait (TO:1000023) which is the color of the sterile lemma (PO:0009040)." [IRRI:SES, PATO:0000014, PO:0009040, TO:cooperl, TO:moorel]

def: "A chemical stress sensitivity (TO:0000482) which is the tolerance exhibited by a plant or a group of plants (population) towards the plant growth hormone." [TO:cooperl]
name: plant growth hormone sensitivity
synonym: ['"growth regulator sensitivity (related)" RELATED []', '"plant hormone response (related)" RELATED []']

comment: Refer to width PATO:0000921: A 1-D extent quality which is equal to the distance from one side of an object to another side which is opposite.
def: "A grain width (TO:0000975) which is the width of the dehulled grain with pericarp (PO:0009084)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, PO:0009084, TO:moorel]
name: dehulled grain width
synonym: ['"dehulled grain curved width (narrow)" NARROW []', '"dehulled grain width (exact)" RELATED []', '"DHULGRWD (exact)" RELATED []', '"GRWD (broad)" RELATED []', '"width of grain without hull (exact)" EXACT []']

def: "Causal agent: Cnaphalocrosis medinalis, Marasmia patnalis. Symptoms: larvae consume the leaf tissue except the epidermis, causing typical white streaks. They create a leaf tube during later stages of feeding. Plant is susceptible and resistant check (if available) after every 10-test entries. Replicate the test three times, if seed is available. Determined by percentage of damaged and folded leaves." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: leaf-folder resistance

def: "Extent of rooting from the nodes on a stem." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: nodal rooting

def: "Causal agent: Nymphula depunctalis. Symptoms: Larvae feed on leaf tissue, leaving only the papery upper epidermis." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: caseworm resistance
synonym: ['"CW (related)" RELATED []', '"CWRS (related)" RELATED []', '"float worm (related)" RELATED []', '"hama putih (indonesian) (related)" RELATED []', '"paddy caseworm (related)" RELATED []']

def: "A panicle morphology trait (TO:0000847) which is the percentage of shattered grains, determined by firmly grasping and pulling the hand over the panicle." [IRRI:SES]
name: panicle threshability

def: "Total protein content of the polished rice." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: polished rice protein content

def: "A caryopsis fruit morphology trait (TO:0001079) which is the ratio of grain length (TO:0000734) to grain width (TO:0002762), including the caryopsis hull (PO:0006000)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: grain length to width ratio

def: "Determined by deducting the peak viscosity from the cool paste viscosity." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal37]
name: setback viscosity

def: "Causal agent: Rice tungro bacilliform virus (RTBV) and rice tungro spherical virus (RTSV). The disease is transmitted by the green leafhopper Nephotettix spp. Symptoms: Yellow-to-yellow orange leaves, stunting and slightly reduced tillering." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES, web:http//www.fao.org/inpho/vlibrary/t0567e/T0567E03.htm]
name: rice tungro virus resistance
white rice protein content
synonym: ['"polished rice protein (related)" RELATED []', '"protein content for polished rice (related)" RELATED []', '"WHTRPROTCN (related)" RELATED []']

comment: An example is CMS-HL in rice.
def: "Abortion at bi-nucleate stage of microspore development." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: aborted bi-nucleate stage

def: "Abortion of the embryo sac leading to female sterility." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]

comment: Refer to pubescent hair (PATO:0001320): A pilosity quality of being covered with short hairs or soft down.
def: "A lemma and palea morphology trait (TO:0000079) which is the extent of pubescence (hairs) on the lemma (PO:0009037) and palea (PO:0009038)." [IRRI:SES, PO:0009037, PO:0009038, TO:moorel]

def: "Causal agent: Gibberella fujikuroi. Symptoms: the plant elongates abnormally, has few tillers and usually dies before producing grains." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]

def: "A leaf morphology trait (TO:0000748) which is a quality of a vascular leaf (PO:0009025)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, PO:0009025, TO:cooperl]

def: "Causal agent: Sphaerulina oryzina (Cercospora janseana)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]
name: narrow brown leaf spot disease resistance

def: "Causal agent: Orseolia oryzae. For the field test to be valid more than 60% of the plants should be affected with not less than 15% silver shoot in the susceptible check. Similarly, 60% of the plants in susceptible check should show silver shoots under green house tests. If any of the test entry in the field evaluation exhibits damage less than 10%, on plant basis, rate it on scale-0, since such a damage could be due to other reasons. Monitor at growth stage 2-5." [IRRI:SES]
name: gall midge resistance

def: "Causal agent: Nilparvata lugens (also Nilaparvata lugens). Symptoms: partial to pronounced yellowing and increasing severity of stunting. Extreme signs are wilting to death of plants. Infested areas in the field may be patchy." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]

def: "A stem internode morphology trait (TO:0000756) which is the color of the stem internode (PO:0020142)." [IRRI:SES, TO:cooperl]

def: "The angle of the culm with respect to the ground surface in a grass plant." [IRRI:SES]
name: culm angle

def: "Plant sensitivity observed in response to different concentrations of salt in the growth medium." [IRRI:SES]
name: salt sensitivity

def: "Rate of germination of the seed." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: germination rate

comment: Refers to length (PATO:0000122): A 1-D extent quality which is equal to the distance between two points. In maize, this is measured in centimeters.
def: "An ear infructescence morphology trait (TO:0000976) that is the length of an ear infructescence (PO:0025597) from base to tip." [TO:cooperl]
name: ear length

def: "Response by the plant in terms of sensitivity to temperature stress." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]

comment: Refers to diameter (PATO:0001334): A length quality which is equal to the length of any straight line segment that passes through the center of a circle and whose endpoints are on the circular boundary. In maize, this is measured in centimeters.

def: "Determined by counting the filled and unfilled spikelets of the bagged grass inflorescence." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, IRRI:SES]

def: "In plants, it represents the incompetence of the pollen to fertilize the ovum. Reasons could be non-viable pollen, incompatibility, pollen abortion, toxicity, genetic etc. Usually determined by either the pollen sterility or spikelet fertility (percent seed set)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: male sterility
synonym: ['"degree of male sterility of male sterile lines (related)" RELATED []', '"male sterility measure (related)" RELATED []', '"MALEST (related)" RELATED []']

comment: It represents the damage done by the diease and/or the pathogen to the plant. The damage is a direct measure of resistance to the particular fungal strain causing the disease.
def: "The resistance exhibited by a plant or a group of plants (population) in response to the disease caused by a fungal pathogen infection as compared to the susceptible and/or the reference plants of the same species." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: fungal disease resistance

def: "Number of grains (full grain with hull) present in one plant." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal37]
name: grain number per plant

def: "Fresh weight of the plant." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal37]
name: plant fresh weight

comment: To be used only for traits from maize.
def: "An infructescence yield trait (TO:0000936) that is the number of ears (ear infructescence; PO:0025597) on a plant or the average number present in population." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, TO:cooperl]
name: ear infructescence number
synonym: ['"ear number per plant (related)" RELATED []', '"EARNB (related)" RELATED []', '"ears per 10 plants (related)" RELATED []', '"ears per plant (related)" RELATED []', '"ENO (related)" RELATED []', '"ENP (related)" RELATED []']

def: "A fruit morphology trait (TO:0002629) which is the number of seeds (PO:0009010) in a fruit (PO:0009001)." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal, PO:0009001, PO:0009010]
name: fruit seed number

comment: May be a response to abiotic stress. If you are annotating to this term, please add an additional annotation to vascular leaf morphology (TO:0000419) or non-vascular leaf morphology trait (TO:0000925), depending on the species.
def: "A leaf morphology trait (TO:0000748) which is the drying of a leaf (PO:0025034)." [PO:0025034, TO:cooperl, TO:moorel]

comment: Another trait seed number (TO:0000445) is directly associated with it.

name: filled grain number
synonym: ['"FGRNB (exact)" EXACT []', '"FILGRNB (related)" RELATED []', '"filled fruit number (related)" RELATED []', '"filled grain number per panicle (exact)" EXACT []', '"grain number per panicle (sensu Oryza) (related)" RELATED []', '"GRNBPPN (related)" RELATED []', '"number of grains per panicle (exact)" EXACT []']

def: "Determined by counting the percent spikelets filled with grain in one grass inflorescence (panicle) or plant." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: filled grain percentage
synonym: ['"FGRPCENT (related)" RELATED []', '"Filled grain percent per panicle (related)" RELATED []']

def: "Average weight of dehulled grains per plant." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]
name: grain yield per plant

def: "Average weight of dehulled grains per panicle." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]

def: "A ratio of number of large vascular bundles present in the spikelets to the number of spikelets in a grass inflorescence." [Gramene:pankaj_jaiswal]

comment: Often measured using the flag leaf.
